<task id="t_psdk_ref_configuring-advertising"> 
  <title>Configure clickable ads</title> 
  <shortdesc> 
  </shortdesc> 
  <taskbody> 
	 <context id="context_118E1EC6D13E426CB31E4F415D47D6A5"> 
		<p>The general workflow is as follows: 
		<ol id="ol_07B2DEE1C9CB450D9111C5741C63E58C"> 
		  <li id="li_4D1CB4D058BA47D181D86422F812C0AD">When an ad creative
			 starts, the <ph conref="../../phrase_library.xml#c_psdk_phrase-library/primetime-sdk-name"/> determines if the ad is clickable. 
		  </li> 
		  <li id="li_E02060BB1ABC49CCA670D1AD01C589E1">If the ad is clickable,
			 the player shows a button: "Click here for more info." 
		  </li> 
		  <li id="li_6F7BF8F3AB12451F818753626FA01163">If the user clicks the
			 button, playback is paused and the device launches the default browser and
			 loads the URL returned from the <ph conref="../../phrase_library.xml#c_psdk_phrase-library/primetime-sdk-name"/>. 
		  </li> 
		</ol> 
		</p> 
